He will provide for you from sources you never expected, when you least expect it.

699
01:06:15,599 --> 01:06:25,739
This is the verse I want you to remember: whoever observes righteousness towards God, He

700
01:06:25,739 --> 01:06:29,639
will create an exit for him and provide for him from whence he never expects.

701
01:06:31,420 --> 01:06:34,599
Anyone who trusts in God, God will suffice him.

702
01:06:35,900 --> 01:06:38,400
God always carries out His decrees.

703
01:06:40,500 --> 01:06:45,059
You have come to the conclusion that God is the king, the absolute ruler of the universe,

704
01:06:48,480 --> 01:06:51,519
and He will carry out His promises and His decrees.

705
01:06:55,780 --> 01:07:00,559
You just have to believe it, you must have absolute confidence in it.

706
01:07:01,720 --> 01:07:21,039
Tomorrow there is a mandatory law, the insurance law, and we, as most of you, have decided that you have insurance with God, that if you are with God, you have the best insurance.

707
01:07:21,039 --> 01:07:30,099
And you have to believe that. Nothing will happen to you when you have insurance

708
01:07:30,099 --> 01:07:34,760
with God. This is the assurance. The difference between the insurance companies and God's

709
01:07:34,760 --> 01:07:40,179
insurance. If you have God's insurance, you don't have anything happen to you. Your car,

710
01:07:40,300 --> 01:07:47,820
your health. With the insurance companies, you still have the accidents, and the insurance

711
01:07:47,820 --> 01:07:48,880
company will pay for you.

712
01:07:50,539 --> 01:07:53,659
You have the agony of the accident,

713
01:07:54,380 --> 01:07:58,739
and the inconvenience of losing the car or having an operation,

714
01:08:00,539 --> 01:08:02,059
and the companies will pay.

715
01:08:04,579 --> 01:08:08,039
But you do have to have the confidence that when you have insurance with God,

716
01:08:08,539 --> 01:08:09,699
nothing will happen to you.

717
01:08:10,960 --> 01:08:13,699
Also, you must know that if God wants to get you, He'll get you,

718
01:08:13,739 --> 01:08:14,940
whether you have insurance or not.

719
01:08:18,060 --> 01:08:20,279
You cannot escape from it.

720
01:08:21,380 --> 01:08:23,359
That is to say, if you deserve a pinch,

721
01:08:23,500 --> 01:08:26,300
or a little accident, or a little sickness,

722
01:08:27,800 --> 01:08:30,180
you can't get away, not without being a little uncomfortable.

723
01:08:31,360 --> 01:08:31,840
Yes.

724
01:08:33,600 --> 01:08:34,079
Yes.

725
01:08:38,820 --> 01:08:40,699
When you have to, then you have to.

726
01:08:40,840 --> 01:08:44,640
We will not buy insurance unless we have to.

727
01:08:44,640 --> 01:08:48,039
But it appears that God is already taking care of us.

728
01:08:48,640 --> 01:08:52,220
Because the law enforcement, the prosecutors

729
01:08:52,220 --> 01:08:56,220
are all protesting the law, and they are making an official statement.

730
01:08:57,519 --> 01:09:01,020
They will not enforce it.

731
01:09:01,239 --> 01:09:03,119
They don't want to enforce it.

732
01:09:04,220 --> 01:09:08,539
So, I called the Civil Liberties Union myself, and I told them, this contradicts our

733
01:09:08,539 --> 01:09:12,039
religious beliefs, and everything. And they didn't do anything about it.

734
01:09:13,520 --> 01:09:16,279
So, we will not buy insurance until we have to.

735
01:09:17,460 --> 01:09:22,960
Because the Quran says, if you have to eat pork, or drink wine, or do anything,

736
01:09:23,039 --> 01:09:28,279
if you have to, without being malicious or desiring it, then you are not committing a sin.

737
01:09:34,860 --> 01:09:39,520
But what I'm saying is, when God says, "and provide for you from whence you never expect,"

738
01:09:39,520 --> 01:09:43,359
We must know that. We need to have that confidence.

739
01:09:44,779 --> 01:09:47,680
If you have a slight doubt, it will not work.

740
01:09:50,800 --> 01:09:56,680
And this important statement, we are in it, we have been in it for a long time.

741
01:10:01,100 --> 01:10:06,659
We had that conviction to the extent, I told you about our friend Abdullah Arik on the dais,

742
01:10:06,659 --> 01:10:09,260
I said, "What's the number? What's the number?"

743
01:10:10,880 --> 01:10:13,840
Where? I said I had to go to God for his phone number.

744
01:10:18,780 --> 01:10:22,500
He was just... he wasn't thinking. I mean, it was the natural question

745
01:10:22,500 --> 01:10:25,739
coming from him, but then of course he was,

746
01:10:25,779 --> 01:10:30,640
because he had a pen in his hand and the pen was there

747
01:10:30,640 --> 01:10:34,159
to write the phone number. It was a true test case.

748
01:10:34,159 --> 01:10:36,380
Before the thought could even be collected,

749
01:10:38,000 --> 01:10:40,239
the number was presented to me by God.

750
01:10:40,839 --> 01:10:41,680
And I related it to him.

751
01:10:43,100 --> 01:10:43,659
So,

752
01:10:46,579 --> 01:10:48,439
God is always victorious in His command.

753
01:10:48,720 --> 01:10:50,079
He is the absolute ruler.

754
01:10:50,819 --> 01:10:52,199
He runs this country.

755
01:10:52,739 --> 01:10:54,039
He runs the region.

756
01:10:54,180 --> 01:10:56,640
He runs the government.

757
01:10:56,979 --> 01:10:58,720
And any government, anywhere.

758
01:10:59,060 --> 01:11:00,100
God runs everything.

759
01:11:04,840 --> 01:11:10,920
If you go to the end of verse 4, it says, whoever observes righteousness towards God,

760
01:11:11,100 --> 01:11:13,520
God will make everything easy for him.

761
01:11:15,319 --> 01:11:17,199
Everything will go easy for him.

762
01:11:17,960 --> 01:11:19,600
He will not suffer any hardship.

763
01:11:23,140 --> 01:11:26,180
There is absolutely no humiliation for the servants of God.

764
01:11:28,440 --> 01:11:33,739
You go apply for a job, and you will tip the balance, because your soul takes over the place.

765
01:11:35,080 --> 01:11:42,560
And you see them running to serve you. They may not realize it, but they feel it.

766
01:11:46,060 --> 01:11:50,119
Whoever observes righteousness towards God, God will make everything easy for him.

767
01:11:51,239 --> 01:11:54,920
This is God's promise as documented here in His Final Testament.

768
01:11:55,859 --> 01:12:02,220
So we'll go back now to page 23, about hardship and the mandatory test.

769
01:12:11,100 --> 01:12:19,739
Over and over we see people who are immensely wealthy on the TV and they're complaining about how unhappy they are.

770
01:12:41,819 --> 01:12:49,020
Take all these severe problems, earthquakes, hurricanes, floods,

771
01:12:49,739 --> 01:12:59,920
All these are punishments, tests, because all these things are absolutely controlled by God.

772
01:13:00,840 --> 01:13:04,539
There is a statement that will answer your question.

773
01:13:05,920 --> 01:13:09,300
Surah, I believe, 54, just look up 54.

774
01:13:14,840 --> 01:13:17,680
Surah 64, plus or minus 2 Surahs, I'm going to find it.

775
01:13:24,300 --> 01:13:25,720
Yeah, 64, verse 11.

776
01:13:30,539 --> 01:13:34,739
No disaster strikes except in accordance with God's will.

777
01:13:38,720 --> 01:13:39,920
This is the law.

778
01:13:40,500 --> 01:13:44,340
No disaster strikes except in accordance with God's will.

779
01:13:45,979 --> 01:13:51,779
No pain, no disaster, nothing happens except by personal decree from God.

780
01:13:51,779 --> 01:14:04,979
Because it's not simple, it's not easy to get a simple headache, for example.

781
01:14:06,340 --> 01:14:09,420
It has to be a personal decree from God.

782
01:14:10,239 --> 01:14:11,439
But the question is,

783
01:14:11,439 --> 01:14:15,699
what's the difference between a balaa' and a musibah?

784
01:14:16,380 --> 01:14:17,760
They are not the same.

785
01:14:19,300 --> 01:14:27,079
Do you want to answer the question, anyone?

786
01:14:27,579 --> 01:14:27,939
Yes.

787
01:14:29,060 --> 01:14:30,180
A musibah is a calamity that strikes you.

788
01:14:30,340 --> 01:14:33,060
It is always a hardship.

789
01:14:33,940 --> 01:14:35,439
A balaa', on the other hand, is a test.

790
01:14:35,439 --> 01:14:38,859
It can be through a blessing or through a hardship.

791
01:14:39,520 --> 01:14:40,680
Well, God is accurate.

792
01:14:42,740 --> 01:14:46,819
Every drop of water is measured. Everything in this world is measured.

793
01:14:49,820 --> 01:14:53,500
Every piece of ice that fell on Denver was a given measure, with precision.

794
01:14:54,820 --> 01:14:56,800
It was measured. Yeah.

795
01:14:57,039 --> 01:14:59,399
We see that also, for example, with the Nile.

796
01:14:59,619 --> 01:15:01,979
The whole plan is to make that land even more fertile.

797
01:15:02,340 --> 01:15:04,720
And then when the river overflows its banks,

798
01:15:05,000 --> 01:15:07,380
and when the flood recedes, it leaves the land fertile.

799
01:15:07,380 --> 01:15:15,460
Everything is planned. The minutest detail is very carefully planned, alhamdulillah.

800
01:15:17,020 --> 01:15:25,119
Nothing is coincidental or haphazard. Nothing. As individuals, as nations, as a world.

801
01:15:28,239 --> 01:15:35,420
Just think, every drop of water is measured, exactly where it goes, where it's going to fall.

802
01:15:35,420 --> 01:15:38,899
He knows even about an ant that's crawling on the ground.

803
01:15:39,239 --> 01:15:39,880
That's right.

804
01:15:49,960 --> 01:15:53,119
Okay, Clark, what are the recipients of charity?

805
01:15:58,039 --> 01:16:02,920
They ask you about what to give for charity.

806
01:16:02,920 --> 01:16:08,640
Say, "Charities shall go to the parents, the relatives, the orphans, the poor, and the

807
01:16:08,640 --> 01:16:08,960
traveling alien."

808
01:16:09,340 --> 01:16:13,600
Any righteous work you do, God is fully aware thereof.

809
01:16:15,279 --> 01:16:21,500
Fighting may be forced upon you, though you dislike it. But you may dislike something

810
01:16:21,500 --> 01:16:26,399
which is actually good for you, and you may like something which is actually bad for you.

811
01:16:27,439 --> 01:16:29,399
God knows, while you do not know.

812
01:16:30,199 --> 01:16:35,500
They ask you about desecrating the Sacred Months by fighting therein.

813
01:16:35,920 --> 01:16:39,619
Say, "Fighting therein is a gross offense,

814
01:16:40,460 --> 01:16:44,140
but repelling people from the path of God, and disbelieving in Him,

815
01:16:44,140 --> 01:16:46,619
and desecrating the Sacred Mosque,

816
01:16:46,619 --> 01:16:52,779
and evicting its people therefrom are all greater sacrileges in the sight of God."

817
01:16:53,500 --> 01:16:55,260
Oppression is worse than murder.

818
01:16:55,260 --> 01:17:02,579
They will continue to fight you to revert you from your religion, if they can.

819
01:17:03,560 --> 01:17:08,460
Those who revert from their religion, and die as disbelievers, have nullified their work in

820
01:17:08,460 --> 01:17:12,859
this life and the Hereafter; they will be companions of Hell, wherein they abide forever.

821
01:17:13,640 --> 01:17:20,020
As for those who believe, and those who immigrate and strive in the cause of God, they have deserved God's

822
01:17:20,020 --> 01:17:20,359
mercy.

823
01:17:20,359 --> 01:17:20,460


824
01:17:21,359 --> 01:17:22,920
God is Forgiving, Most Merciful.

825
01:17:24,220 --> 01:17:26,979
There are two different subjects here.

826
01:17:27,579 --> 01:17:38,140
Verse 215 talks about charity, and it tells us specifically that charity first goes

827
01:17:38,140 --> 01:17:43,020
to those that are closest to us, the ones that we are most responsible for: our parents and

828
01:17:43,020 --> 01:17:43,539
our relatives.

829
01:17:44,479 --> 01:17:52,220
And the next are those that really need economic help but don't have someone else to rely on:

830
01:17:52,380 --> 01:17:56,739
orphans, the poor, and the traveling aliens.

831
01:18:01,620 --> 01:18:07,859
So, this is how carefully we are given the details of how submitters are to do this.

832
01:18:09,260 --> 01:18:14,380
First, look to the parents if they need it. If they don't need it, then to the relatives.

833
01:18:14,560 --> 01:18:21,220
In other words, each takes care of their own. And if each one takes care of their own, there will be no misery in the world.

834
01:18:22,259 --> 01:18:40,640
If the relatives are taken care of, then you have the orphans—children who have no parents—then the poor, and then the traveling alien.

835
01:18:45,699 --> 01:18:51,939
Any righteous work that you do, God is fully aware of it. And it seems that charity

836
01:18:51,939 --> 01:19:03,779
is more than just economic help; it can be any kind of help, doing what is right in this world for other people.

837
01:19:03,779 --> 01:19:06,039
This is to simply

838
01:19:06,039 --> 01:19:12,560
enlighten us about anything we do to

839
01:19:12,560 --> 01:19:18,020
make the world better, to treat other people

840
01:19:18,020 --> 01:19:21,359
the way we would like to be treated, with mercy

841
01:19:21,359 --> 01:19:25,779
for the people around us. And then God is...

842
01:19:26,919 --> 01:19:32,300
It's because we want to express God's mercy.

843
01:19:33,779 --> 01:19:51,500
We desire God's forgiveness and God's mercy. And by showing our appreciation for these qualities, we express them to the world around us.

844
01:20:12,380 --> 01:20:19,300
The next subject is on fighting.

845
01:20:21,500 --> 01:20:38,079
Which I take to mean basically in a war-type situation, though it may be... well, when we think of fighting, we think of taking up arms of violence rather than simply arguing.

846
01:20:38,079 --> 01:20:52,680
So, at another level, it could be simply not giving in to any kind of oppression,

847
01:20:52,680 --> 01:20:59,659
which may be economic, or political, or social.

848
01:21:01,099 --> 01:21:06,439
No, I have to say there is only one reason allowed for fighting.

849
01:21:07,520 --> 01:21:11,699
It has to do with the freedom to worship God alone. That's it.

850
01:21:13,720 --> 01:21:17,279
There's absolutely no other reason for fighting.

851
01:21:17,340 --> 01:21:21,920
Only if it's going to interfere with your freedom of religion and the worship of God alone.

852
01:21:25,439 --> 01:21:34,060
Oppression means trying to impose any kind of religious view on you, or to prevent you from practicing your religion.

853
01:22:34,960 --> 01:21:37,819
That is the only ground. The only reason for fighting.

854
01:21:38,579 --> 01:21:42,600
But fighting may be imposed upon you, that somebody comes and says, "Don't pray."

855
01:21:43,960 --> 01:21:46,359
You cannot pray. If you're prevented, you cannot pray.

856
01:21:50,599 --> 01:21:55,920
But if your country gets into war with another country and you're required to go and fight,

857
01:21:56,459 --> 01:21:58,100
if you are drafted or anything?

858
01:21:58,479 --> 01:22:00,800
No, you don't fight because of land, even if you're drafted.

859
01:22:03,140 --> 01:22:03,659
Unless they attack you.

860
01:22:03,659 --> 01:22:06,779
Yeah, if the other country is trying to make you not believe in God.

861
01:22:07,359 --> 01:22:11,760
But if Russia comes to invade this country for the purpose of expelling everyone who's an atheist,

862
01:22:12,939 --> 01:22:14,659
then that's in the cause of God.

863
01:22:14,859 --> 01:22:16,340
The only fighting is in the cause of God.

864
01:22:16,340 --> 01:22:17,960
Not because of country and not because of land.

865
01:22:18,399 --> 01:22:20,520
So whatever, whatever the reason,

866
01:22:20,520 --> 01:22:22,239
whatever the circumstance—

867
01:22:22,239 --> 01:22:22,760
fighting

868
01:22:25,179 --> 01:22:26,380
for land,

869
01:22:26,380 --> 01:22:28,119
because of a

870
01:22:28,119 --> 01:22:29,739
border, because of country—

871
01:22:30,340 --> 01:22:30,920
is all

872
01:22:30,920 --> 01:22:33,079
a waste of life.

873
01:22:33,539 --> 01:22:36,100
Because God did not create this border.

874
01:22:36,920 --> 01:22:37,800
People created

875
01:22:37,800 --> 01:22:38,659
these in the past.

876
01:22:39,600 --> 01:22:41,539
When are you forced to defend yourself

877
01:22:41,539 --> 01:22:43,199
if somebody else

878
01:22:43,199 --> 01:22:44,800
wants to take your land?

879
01:22:46,940 --> 01:22:51,199
You have the choice to fight, or you just, you know, run away.

880
01:22:51,539 --> 01:22:52,300
Well, it's up to you.

881
01:22:53,180 --> 01:22:57,859
It doesn't, uh, it's not a command from God to do it.

882
01:23:00,380 --> 01:23:04,640
Well, yeah, I mean, if as it says about evicting you from your houses,

883
01:23:04,680 --> 01:23:07,340
you evict them from where they evicted you,

884
01:23:07,460 --> 01:23:11,340
it may be, you know, if they're simply fighting not...

885
01:23:11,340 --> 01:23:16,859
they're not persecuting you religiously, but, say, they're just grabbing land,

886
01:23:16,859 --> 01:23:19,560
is a political difference in...

887
01:23:20,220 --> 01:23:22,819
Did we, did we go through the rules of war yet?

888
01:23:23,400 --> 01:23:25,220
Because, uh, that doesn't qualify as war.

889
01:23:31,860 --> 01:23:33,199
Did we go through that?

890
01:23:33,740 --> 01:23:34,840
It was a great thing.

891
01:23:34,899 --> 01:23:36,479
Yeah, yeah, we did, yeah, we did.

892
01:23:47,000 --> 01:23:52,539
that those rules of war, they say, "Do not fight them at the Sacred Mosque, unless they

893
01:23:52,539 --> 01:23:53,359
attack you first."

894
01:23:59,920 --> 01:24:06,720
I don't want somebody to come and say, "You can't practice this religion," you know, this

895
01:24:06,720 --> 01:24:08,760
is where we have to fight that.

896
01:24:09,079 --> 01:24:10,439
